The incident happened on Sunday noon after the deceased were found in a bush with nine cows stolen from Gesari village in the neighbouring district of Serengeti. Their names are yet to be identified but they are aged between 35-40 years.They were killed with traditional weapons by citizens after finding them in the bush with nine cows they had stolen , reads part of the press release issued by Tarime Rorya Regional Police Commander Senior Assistant Commissioner of Police (SACP) Henry Mwaibambe.The bodies of the deceased were until Monday afternoon being preserved at Tarime District Hospital Mortuary, according to the statement. SACP Mwaibambe urged residents here to stop punishing criminal suspects and instead take them to state agencies for the law to take its course.